Property_Method.name: IBizTalkApplication
Property_Method.summary: Represents a BizTalk Application. An application is a logical grouping or container of artifacts.

Property_Method.name: AddReference
Property_Method.summary: Adds a reference to an application. The AddReference method will detect potential circular reference and throw an exception if this situation happens. For example, if application A references B, and B references C, then user cannot add A to B's references or to C's references.
Property_Method.param: The application object to which a reference has to be made.

Property_Method.name: RemoveReference
Property_Method.summary: Removes a reference to an application.
Property_Method.param: The application object which has to be un-referenced.

Property_Method.name: Start
Property_Method.summary: Starts all orchestrations, sendports and sendport groups, and enables all receive locations belonging to the application and its references.
Property_Method.param: The Application start options. Specify one or more flags defined in the ApplicationStartOption enum.

Property_Method.name: Stop
Property_Method.summary: Stops all orchestrations, sendports and sendport groups, and disables all receive locations belonging to the application and its references.
Property_Method.param: The Application stop options. Specify one or more flags defined in the ApplicationStopOption enum.

Property_Method.name: AddNewSendPort
Property_Method.summary: Creates and adds a send port to the send port collection.
Property_Method.param: Specify true for dynamic port.
Specify true for two way ports.
Property_Method.returns: Returns the newly created send port.

Property_Method.name: AddNewReceivePort
Property_Method.summary: Creates and adds a receive port to the receive port collection.
Property_Method.param: Specify true to create a two-way receive port, specify false to create a one-way receive port.
Property_Method.returns: Returns the newly created receive port.

Property_Method.name: AddNewSendPortGroup
Property_Method.summary: Creates and adds a send port group to the send port group collection.
Property_Method.returns: Returns the newly created send port group.

Property_Method.name: Name
Property_Method.summary: Gets the Application's name.

Property_Method.name: Description
Property_Method.summary: Gets the Application's description.

Property_Method.name: IsDefaultApplication
Property_Method.summary: Returns true if the Application is the default Application.

Property_Method.name: IsSystem
Property_Method.summary: Returns true if the Application is the BizTalk System Application.

Property_Method.name: IsStarted
Property_Method.summary: This property indicates the status of the Application. It returns true if all the orchestrations, sendports and sendport groups in the Application are started, and all receive locations in the Application are enabled. Returns false if at least one of the artifacts is stopped or disabled. Note that if there are no artifacts in the Application IsStarted returns true.

Property_Method.name: IsConfigured
Property_Method.summary: This property indicates the configuration status of the Application. It returns true if the logical ports of all the orchestrations in the Application are bound.

Property_Method.summary: Returns the collection of Applications that are referenced by this Application. This collection only the goes one level deep, so to find all the dependencies one has to recursively go through this collection.
